      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09A\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy the decision table rows into table `J09A_temp` where the tour starts with `J09A`.\\n\\n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09A_temp`.\\n\\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `J09A_temp`:\\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA` when a `HAUS` has fewer than 3 `EQUNR`.\\n   - Else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`.\\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU` for all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0`.\\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU` for all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` from `500` to `599`.\\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU` for all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` from `900` to `999`.\\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU` for all houses in address area `Wiblingwerde` or `Breckerfeld`.\\n\\n4. Join `J09A_temp` with table `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\\n\\n5. Join the result with `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\\n\\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\\n\\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\\n   1. Use the customer table entries from `SALES_MASTER`.\\n   Else:\\n   1. Use the customer table entries from `NET_MASTER`.\\n\\n8. Identify households with mandatory meter reading:\\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `MANDATORY_READING` for every `EQUNR` in `EABL` where both conditions are true:\\n     - `ISTABLART_TXT = \\\"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\\\"` and the record was created in `2024`\\n     - `ISTABLART_TXT = \\\"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\\\"` and the record was created in `2023`\\n\\n9. Export all rows with `ENTSCHEIDUNG = MANDATORY_READING` as CSV file `J09A_MANDATORY_READING` with columns:\\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\\n\\n10. Send `J09A_MANDATORY_READING.csv` to the internal team:\\n    - email_address: `mandatory.reading@provider.com`\\n    - file_path: `<file path for J09A_MANDATORY_READING.csv here>`\\n\\n11. Export the final data excluding all `MANDATORY_READING` rows as CSV file `J09A` with columns:\\n    `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\\n\\n12. Send the CSV file to EVU:\\n    - Email address: `meter.readings@evu.com`\\n    - file_path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`\\n\\n13. Delete the temporary table.\"}",
            "id": "lc_a0c28e43-dfb1-4fce-9ebc-e9651bcd8133"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "6cfcda76-f1e2-4285-8c41-b14a3db77926",
        "tool_call_id": "call_XaZ3PAILVSvckPo8WxvO51p5",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09A",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy the decision table rows into table `J09A_temp` where the tour starts with `J09A`.\n\n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09A_temp`.\n\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `J09A_temp`:\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA` when a `HAUS` has fewer than 3 `EQUNR`.\n   - Else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`.\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU` for all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0`.\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU` for all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` from `500` to `599`.\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU` for all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` from `900` to `999`.\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU` for all houses in address area `Wiblingwerde` or `Breckerfeld`.\n\n4. Join `J09A_temp` with table `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\n\n5. Join the result with `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\n\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\n\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\n   1. Use the customer table entries from `SALES_MASTER`.\n   Else:\n   1. Use the customer table entries from `NET_MASTER`.\n\n8. Identify households with mandatory meter reading:\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `MANDATORY_READING` for every `EQUNR` in `EABL` where both conditions are true:\n     - `ISTABLART_TXT = \"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\"` and the record was created in `2024`\n     - `ISTABLART_TXT = \"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\"` and the record was created in `2023`\n\n9. Export all rows with `ENTSCHEIDUNG = MANDATORY_READING` as CSV file `J09A_MANDATORY_READING` with columns:\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\n\n10. Send `J09A_MANDATORY_READING.csv` to the internal team:\n    - email_address: `mandatory.reading@provider.com`\n    - file_path: `<file path for J09A_MANDATORY_READING.csv here>`\n\n11. Export the final data excluding all `MANDATORY_READING` rows as CSV file `J09A` with columns:\n    `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\n\n12. Send the CSV file to EVU:\n    - Email address: `meter.readings@evu.com`\n    - file_path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`\n\n13. Delete the temporary table."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
